	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok i am just gonna say some stuff about necros from my exp here.  First off about the partnering up.  Its a really good idea.  In dl i got my best exp from grouping up with another.  Necros best parter imho is rogue.  I mean what more can you ask for than adding a heavy dmge dealer with the backstab attack.  All i would do is pull with darkness then fear and med  i once counted 30 kills before i ever had to med out for a few.  Indeed awesome exp.  Of course you will find partners who dont do as well or dont damage as good but this was my best exp partnering up.  In dl 30 kills before ever having to med with 2 people is pretty damn good.  Another thing i thought i would point out is a very unlikely but great group experience.  The group had 3 mages, 2 necros and 1 chanter.  constant pulling nothing died best exp i have ever got in group there.  It was kinda funny seeing 5 pets tear a mob up and even though lots of pets great exp.  I went to dl at lvl 43 almost 44 and at 48 alot of things green out.  So at 49 i am moving somewhere else. Just some tips for dl.. Soloing can be very tricky here.  Dont pull spiders.  I did once and got my ass rooted and killed.  They also seem to resist more than other mobs there. Was too far from pet to help.  If you do want to kill spiders put shadowstep up so you can get away from it while rooted.  The best and safest things to pull are cockatrices, drovlargs, brutes and giant.  Dont attempt the ravishing drovlargs unless you are fm and are at least 44..  very tough mob indeed.  Oh yea i read somewhere about soloin past 40 jboots are a must.  Very true.  As bad as you hate it camp the mfer in sro and be patient.  Either that or spend lots of money on sow potions.  But for soloers they are very very helpful.<br><br>  Collect words always.  Always auction for words people dont want.  Chances are you can have all your words for spells by time you lvl.  Ones you dont need  give to one who does.  Dont wait til you ding to get words.  Its horrible.  And another thing go to all gm events ya can.  I went to my first in nro and got a drake scale braclet first  and went back another day and got a cloak of the mind.  Both good items to have and was better than what i did have.  Was told there was still a helmet for casters that dropped also.  Cheers to VI for doin this.  it certainly adds some excitement to game.  There is nothing like running around a desert like a moron killing everything you see.  Its like a race.  Very fun.  Ok sorry to go on about so much.  I will post more as my mind clears.<br>&nbsp;<br>Sphoenix Darkfever</td></tr>
