<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100495914111272></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100495914111272><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100495914111272>RE: nec</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100495914111272#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=49677><span id=Sage>alaaraaf the Puissant</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>111 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 5th 6:19 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.93]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey.<br><br>If you're solo'ing with the pet and it does all the damage, you should get 50% of the EXP.  The pet gets the other half.  Essentially, if the pet does more damage than you, it takes 50%.  If you do more damage, it takes about 1%.<br><br>If you're in a group, this is a little different.  The pet should be taking a flat rate 1% of the group's EXP.  (It'd be pretty sad if the pet was out damaging the whole group anyhow.)  <br><br>HOWEVER...<br><br>If you are in a group and you do nothing, you will be awarded with no EXP.  I don't know, (because I have never tested this part,) but I would guess that if you do nothing but send in the pet, this probably still stands.<br><br>The other thing to consider is that creatures are not all the same level.  So, if you are hunting something that is at the bottom end of the creatures that will give you EXP, you won't necessarilly always get EXP.  For example, at L41, stalag terrors mostly still give EXP.  But, the lowest level ones don't.  So, every so often you kill one that gives nothing.<br><br>Hope that helps.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br>"Death is coming..."<br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
