<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100474002231879></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100474002231879><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100474002231879>RE: Kiting?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100474002231879#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>108 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Nov 2nd 5:27 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.36]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Kiting ....<br><br>kiting, kiting, kiting.<br><br>Kiting is basically the process of demolishing a MOB from a distance while it is running (either towards you or away from you).  Certain classes can kite, and some much better than others.  As such, there are several different types of kiting used by different classes.  Such as ....<br><br>Druid kiting.  Druids can kite by using their sow spells (making themselves run fast), snare spells (making the enemy run slow), and root spell (stopping the MOB altogether).  I've never actually played a druid, so flame me if I'm wrong, but the basic spell would go something like:  make sure you have sow on, snare or root MOB, apply DDs and/or DoTs as necessary, back off keeping the MOB at a good safe distance, reapply DoTs, DDs, snare as needed.  I've also seen them root the MOB to get themselves some meditation time.  A note on druids, they get some nasty area of effect spells which enable them to quad kite.  Basically the same process but with 4 MOBs in tow instead of just one and use AoE spells to hit them all at once.  Again, correct me if any of this is wrong though.<br><br>Necro kiting.   Necros are the kings of fear kiting, where the MOB is snared (using one of the darkness spells), the necro pet is sicked on the MOB, and then the MOB is feared.  Usually, any number of DoT spells will be added to the feared MOB to increase the damage as needed.  Again, any spell refreshing will be done as needed also, as fear is a random duration and darkness will wear off eventually.<br><br>Other classes can kite.  Rangers can do something similar to druids but usually use bows to do more distance damage since their spells will be inferior to druid's as far as level goes.  Wizards can kite and apparently can also quad kite with AoE spells as well, but I'm not sure when or if they get their snare spell.  Maybe they can only kite when they have sow, i'm not really sure about them.<br><br>I'm probably missing a lot here but those are the basics of kiting as far as I know.<br><br>-Yizzelar<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
